OL,6,FThe editorial justification is obvious
OL,7,Fbut the split between the east and
OL,8,Fwest of Scotland is not as
OL,9,Fstraightforward as many other sub-opts.
OL,11,FThe Edinburgh service is carried from
OL,12,Fthe Craigkelly transmitter and its
OL,13,Frelays.
OL,15,FHowever some viewers in Edinburgh have
OL,16,Ftheir aerials directed towards
OL,17,FBlackhill.
OL,19,FThe Haddington relay to the east of
OL,20,FEdinburgh takes the Blackhill signal.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/8
